{"lemma":"أَعْوَج","slug":"أَعْوَج","root":"ع.#.ج","root_slug":"ع-_-ج","root_link":"/words/roots/ع-_-ج","pos":"ADJ","pos_camel":"adj","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":1},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["","n30923"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B9%D9%92%D9%88%D9%8E%D8%AC"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"crooked, bent, twisted, distorted"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Color or defect adjective from the root ع و ج (ʕ w j).\n\nSee the etymology of the corresponding lemma form."},"ipa":["/ʔaʕ.wad͡ʒ/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n30923","headword_ar":"اَعْوَجُ","root":"Ewj","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crooked, curved, bent,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending, winding, wry, contorted, distorted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"uneven:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, * O, * L, Msb:) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEowaj~N","text_ar":"مُعْوَجٌّ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", [or this and the former also,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked, curved,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of itself:"},{"kind":"text","text":"fem. of the former"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawojaA='u","text_ar":"عَوْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (L, Msb:) and pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwjN","text_ar":"عُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (L.) One says ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaSFA muEowaj~apN","text_ar":"عَصًا مُعْوَجَّةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooking, staff"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"stick"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; but not"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"miEowaj~apN","text_ar":"مِعْوَجَّةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", with kesr to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"m","text_ar":"م"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, O:) or, accord. to ISk, one says the former; but not ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaw~ajapN","text_ar":"مُعَوَّجَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with fet-h to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"E","text_ar":"ع"},{"kind":"text","text":"and teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":"; though analogy does not forbid this, as it is allowable to say"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eaw~ajahaA","text_ar":"عَوَّجَهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":": accord. to As, one should not say ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"muEaw~ajN","text_ar":"مُعَوَّجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", with teshdeed to the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"w","text_ar":"و"},{"kind":"text","text":", except in applying it to a stick, or in another sense expl. below: Az says that this word is allowable as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rendered crooked"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. (Msb.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEawojaA='u","text_ar":"العَوْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The bow."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawojaA='u","text_ar":"عَوْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a woman,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Inclining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"bending, towards her child, to suckle it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And, so applied,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"That has become crooked by reason of leanness and hunger."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Ham p. 744.) And, applied to a she-camel,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Lean, lank, light of flesh, slender,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"lank in the belly:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"emaciated so that her back has become crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b4-  [And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"hilaAl","text_ar":"هِلَال"},{"kind":"text","text":"(or new moon),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Oblique:"},{"kind":"text","text":"see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adofaqu","text_ar":"اَدْفَقُ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b5-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"naxiylN EuwjN","text_ar":"نَخِيلٌ عُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Palm-trees inclining,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"leaning, and therefore crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curved:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and accord. to some, the saying of Lebeed, describing a [wild] he-ass and his she-asses,"},{"kind":"quote","text":"waA^aworadahaA EalaY EuwjK TiwaAli"},{"kind":"text","text":"[the latter hemistich of a verse cited in the first paragraph of art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hw*","text_ar":"حوذ"},{"kind":"text","text":"] means,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And he brought them to the watering-place at"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tall"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm-trees"},{"kind":"text","text":"growing over the water,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"inclining and curving"},{"kind":"text","text":"by reason of the abundance of their fruit: but others say that the meaning of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ElY Ewj","text_ar":"على عوج"},{"kind":"text","text":"is,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon"},{"kind":"text","text":"their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crooked legs."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b6-  Hence,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwjN","text_ar":"عُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"legs"},{"kind":"text","text":"of a horse or similar beast; (O, TA;) as ISd says, thus used as an epithet in which the quality of a subst. predominates [app. implying their"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having that bending,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"curving, and tension of the sinews, termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajoniyb","text_ar":"تَجْنِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":", agreeably with what here follows]. (TA.) ―         -b7-  And hence also, (TA,)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xayolN EuwjN","text_ar":"خَيْلٌ عُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"meaning"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Horses that have, in their hind legs, the quality termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tajoniyb","text_ar":"تَجْنِيب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (A, TA. *) ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"applied to a man means ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Crooked in temper,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"evil in natural disposition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almil~apu AlEawojaA='u","text_ar":"المِلَّةُ العَوْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The crooked,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"perverted,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"corrupted, religion"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a phrase occurring in a trad., applied to the religion of Abraham as changed by the Arabs from its state of rectitude. (TA.) And one says"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"xuT~apN EawojaA='u","text_ar":"خُطَّةٌ عَوْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^oYN A^aEowaju","text_ar":"رَاْىٌ اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", meaning ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"An affair,"},{"kind":"text","text":"and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"an opinion,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not of a right kind."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlA^ay~aAmu EuwjN rawaAjiEu","text_ar":"الاَيَّامُ عُوجٌ رَوَاجِعُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The days are apt to decline from the right course, apt to return,"},{"kind":"text","text":"] is a prov., (Meyd, O, TA,) meaning fortune at one time declines from thee, and at another time returns to thee; (Meyd;) said by him at whose affliction one rejoices, or said on his part, and sometimes on an occasion of threatening: Az says that"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwjN","text_ar":"عُوجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", here, may be pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":", or of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EawojaA='u","text_ar":"عَوْجَا=ءُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; or it may be pl. of ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EaAy^ijN","text_ar":"عَايِجٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and originally"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EuwujN","text_ar":"عُوُجٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (O, TA.) [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEuwju","text_ar":"العُوجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is used as signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The days"},{"kind":"text","text":"[in allusion to their variableness with respect to good and evil]. (TA.) ―         -b11-  And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEowaju","text_ar":"اَعْوَجُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is a [proper] name of"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A watering-trough."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA.) ―         -b12-  See also the next paragraph, in four places."}],"source_refs":["L","Msb","S","O","A","K","TA","Meyd"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}